Orange Academy says it is partnering with the University of Lagos Human Resources Development Centre to offer interested participants a four-day workshop on business writing. The academy said in a statement that seasoned professionals would speak at the workshop scheduled for May. The academy quoted UNILAG’s Director of HRDC, Dr Lateef Odekunle, as saying, “The collaboration is a positive development in competence and skills building.” The spokesperson for Orange Academy, Femi Odukoya, said, “Our timely collaboration with the Human Resources Development Centre of UNILAG is coming on the heels of the growing demand to help businesses adapt to the ever-changing environment, most especially in a post-COVID time. “This business writing workshop is an affirmation of our quest to nurture the inner mind to tell stories that can change businesses, brands and people for good.”